<paragraph id="E939A14CFFC1FFD1FF67FD45FD8E74A9" blockId="10.[151,736,628,687]" box="[151,514,662,687]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<figureCitation id="71BDBDC9FFC1FFD1FF67FD45FF5074A9" box="[151,220,662,687]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1515,1538]" captionTargetBox="[201,1391,383,1482]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[181,1405,338,1491]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Distribution of the examined material of the collected hoverfly species in Iran. 1: ■, Pocota hyrcanica Gilasian &amp; Hauser sp. nov.; ●, Sphiximorpha ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. 2: ■, Barchypalpus valgus (Panzer); ●, Cheilosia vicina (Zetterstedt); ▲, Criorhina ranunculi (Panzer); ♦, Eristalis alpina (Panzer); ♣, Eristalis pertinax (Scopoli). 3: ■, Merodon brevis Paramonov; ●, Merodon quadrinotatus (Sack); ▲, Merodon serrulatus Wiedemann; ♦, Merodon schachti Hurkmans; ♣, Merodon vandergooti Hurkmans; ♠, Merodon velox Loew. 4: ■, Neoascia annexa (Müller); ●, Palumbia eristaloides (Portschinsky); ▲, Pseudodoros nigricollis Becker." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/840456/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="71BDBDC9FFC1FFD1FF1AFD44FEBE74A9" box="[234,306,662,687]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 27" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[200,1397,217,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[163,1427,193,1933]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 27. Sphiximorpha spp. 24: Male genitalia of S. ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. in dorsal view, holotype 25: Male genitalia of S. euprosopa (Loew) in dorsal view. 26: Male genitalia of S. ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. in lateral view, holotype 27: Male genitalia of S. euprosopa (Loew) in lateral view. Scale bars 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/840466/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">24, 26</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="71BDBDC9FFC1FFD1FECEFD44FE3D74A9" box="[318,433,663,687]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[223,1352,231,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[197,1396,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 34. Sphiximorpha spp. 28 – 32. S. ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. (male holotype). 28: Adult, dorsal view. 29: Adult, lateral view. 30: Head, lateral view. 31: Head, dorsal view. 32: Head, frontal view. 33: S. euprosopa (Loew) (male), head, frontal view. 34: S. ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. (male holotype), wing. Scale bars 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/840468/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">28–32, 34</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="71BDBDC9FFC1FFD1FE4CFD45FD8E74A9" box="[444,514,662,687]" captionStart="FIGURES 35 – 41" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1806,1829]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,209,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,195,1783]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 35 – 41. Habitat of Sphiximorpha ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. and detail of the dominant plant species in this habitat. 35: Khabr (Keyber) Mountain, Baft, Kerman, Iran. 36: Crataegus songarica. 37: Pistacia atlantica. 38: Pistacia khinjuk. 39: Amygdalus scoparia. 40: Ephedra major. 41: Juniperus excelsa." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/840470/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">35–41</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A19CF2C7FFC1FFD1FF67FD0DFACE75A8" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E939A14CFFC1FFD1FF67FD0DFACE75A8" blockId="10.[151,1437,734,1917]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="DBF27D5EFFC1FFD1FF67FD0DFEE774F1" bold="true" box="[151,363,734,759]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Species diagnosis.</emphasis>
Face with a distinctive median yellow and black pattern; facial median yellow macula bilobed ventrally, extending dorsally to antennal insertions; posterolateral arms of facial black macula broadened apically; antennal length ratio: 1.6: 1: 1.6; posteroapical portion of 1st basal cell (br) and most part of 2nd basal cell (bm) bare, tergite 3 with a pair of faint greyish crescent shaped pollinose fasciae (in dorsal view); dorsal lobe of surstylus, in lateral view, nearly 2.7 times longer than wide and, in dorsal view, with a distinct median U-shaped bend on inner side; cercus semirectangular in lateral view and distinctly broadened medially in dorsal view (
<figureCitation id="71BDBDC9FFC1FFD1FB43FC46FABA75A8" box="[1203,1334,917,942]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 27" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[200,1397,217,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[163,1427,193,1933]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 27. Sphiximorpha spp. 24: Male genitalia of S. ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. in dorsal view, holotype 25: Male genitalia of S. euprosopa (Loew) in dorsal view. 26: Male genitalia of S. ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. in lateral view, holotype 27: Male genitalia of S. euprosopa (Loew) in lateral view. Scale bars 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/840466/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Figs 24, 26</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A19CF2C7FFC1FFD1FF37FC6AFCB9717B" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" type="description">
<paragraph id="E939A14CFFC1FFD1FF37FC6AFCB9717B" blockId="10.[151,1437,734,1917]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="DBF27D5EFFC1FFD1FF37FC6AFE3175D4" bold="true" box="[199,445,953,978]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
Description. 
<collectionCode id="8F973989FFC1FFD1FE92FC6AFE3475D4" box="[354,440,953,978]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">MALE</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
Body length = 
<quantity id="2E7E0CA9FFC1FFD1FD85FC69FD5275D7" box="[629,734,954,978]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.03" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="10.3">10.3 mm</quantity>
; wing length = 
<quantity id="2E7E0CA9FFC1FFD1FC67FC69FC5675D7" box="[919,986,954,978]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation id="71BDBDC9FFC1FFD1FC1BFC6AFBFD75D4" box="[1003,1137,953,978]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[223,1352,231,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[197,1396,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 34. Sphiximorpha spp. 28 – 32. S. ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. (male holotype). 28: Adult, dorsal view. 29: Adult, lateral view. 30: Head, lateral view. 31: Head, dorsal view. 32: Head, frontal view. 33: S. euprosopa (Loew) (male), head, frontal view. 34: S. ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. (male holotype), wing. Scale bars 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/840468/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Figs 28–29</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="DBF27D5EFFC1FFD1FB76FC6AFB4875D4" bold="true" box="[1158,1220,953,978]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71BDBDC9FFC1FFD1FB25FC6AFAD775D4" box="[1237,1371,953,978]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[223,1352,231,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[197,1396,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 34. Sphiximorpha spp. 28 – 32. S. ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. (male holotype). 28: Adult, dorsal view. 29: Adult, lateral view. 30: Head, lateral view. 31: Head, dorsal view. 32: Head, frontal view. 33: S. euprosopa (Loew) (male), head, frontal view. 34: S. ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. (male holotype), wing. Scale bars 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/840468/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Figs 30–32</figureCitation>
). Eye contiguity half as long as pedicel; ocellar triangle black; frons yellow, with anteromedian black moustache-shaped macula limited to dorsal section of frontal prominence; frontal prominence orange; face with a distinctive median yellow and black pattern; facial median yellow macula bilobed ventrally, extending dorsally to antennal insertions; posterolateral arms of facial black macula broadened apically; face almost 3/5 as wide as head medially; antenna predominantly brownish orange, scape paler, terminal stylus narrow, yellow in apical half and dark brown in basal half; scape and pedicel covered with adpressed brownish pile; length ratio: 1.6: 1: 1.6; occiput yellow in dorsal third and covered with greyish pollinosity in ventral 2/3, along eye margin. 
<emphasis id="DBF27D5EFFC1FFD1FBCBFB66FB1D72C8" bold="true" box="[1083,1169,1205,1230]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71BDBDC9FFC1FFD1FB57FB66FAA172C8" box="[1191,1325,1205,1230]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[223,1352,231,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[197,1396,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 34. Sphiximorpha spp. 28 – 32. S. ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. (male holotype). 28: Adult, dorsal view. 29: Adult, lateral view. 30: Head, lateral view. 31: Head, dorsal view. 32: Head, frontal view. 33: S. euprosopa (Loew) (male), head, frontal view. 34: S. ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. (male holotype), wing. Scale bars 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/840468/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Figs 28–29</figureCitation>
). Thorax predominantly shiny black, scutum black, covered uniformly with short white pile; postalar callus brown laterally; postpronotum, notopleuron, posterior 2/3 of anepisternum and about dorsal 1/3 of katepisternum yellow; proepisternum, anterodorsal portion of proepimeron, anepisternum, dorsal and ventral portions of katepisternum with two separate patches of pile; anepimeron with short yellowish pile; scutellum yellow in dorsal view except for a narrow black basal margin. 
<emphasis id="DBF27D5EFFC1FFD1FE15FABAFDAD7384" bold="true" box="[485,545,1385,1410]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71BDBDC9FFC1FFD1FDC2FABAFD0B7384" box="[562,647,1385,1410]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[223,1352,231,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[197,1396,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 34. Sphiximorpha spp. 28 – 32. S. ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. (male holotype). 28: Adult, dorsal view. 29: Adult, lateral view. 30: Head, lateral view. 31: Head, dorsal view. 32: Head, frontal view. 33: S. euprosopa (Loew) (male), head, frontal view. 34: S. ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. (male holotype), wing. Scale bars 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/840468/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
). Anterior margin of wing brownish up to vena spuria; predominantly microtrichose; posteroapical portion of 1st basal cell (br) and most part of 2nd basal cell (bm) bare; basal part of posterior cubital cell and anal lobe with scattered microtrichia; alula predominantly bare, narrowly microtrichose on anterior margin; calypters yellow; halter yellow, basal third black. 
<emphasis id="DBF27D5EFFC1FFD1FC45FA0AFC6773F6" bold="true" box="[949,1003,1497,1520]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71BDBDC9FFC1FFD1FC0CFA0BFBC373F6" box="[1020,1103,1496,1521]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[223,1352,231,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[197,1396,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 34. Sphiximorpha spp. 28 – 32. S. ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. (male holotype). 28: Adult, dorsal view. 29: Adult, lateral view. 30: Head, lateral view. 31: Head, dorsal view. 32: Head, frontal view. 33: S. euprosopa (Loew) (male), head, frontal view. 34: S. ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. (male holotype), wing. Scale bars 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/840468/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
). Coxae black; protrochanter brownish; femora predominantly shiny black, yellow at base and apex; basal 1/3–2/5 of hind femur yellow; tibiae yellow in basal 1/2–2/3 and at apex (rest of tibiae shiny black); tarsi predominantly yellow, tarsomeres 1–4 of hind tarsus distinctly black dorsally; dorso-apical pile of tarsomere 5 black in hind tarsus. 
<emphasis id="DBF27D5EFFC1FFD1FB77F997FB79705B" bold="true" box="[1159,1269,1604,1629]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71BDBDC9FFC1FFD1FAF8F997FA01705B" box="[1288,1421,1604,1629]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[223,1352,231,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[197,1396,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 34. Sphiximorpha spp. 28 – 32. S. ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. (male holotype). 28: Adult, dorsal view. 29: Adult, lateral view. 30: Head, lateral view. 31: Head, dorsal view. 32: Head, frontal view. 33: S. euprosopa (Loew) (male), head, frontal view. 34: S. ziegleri Gilasian &amp; Vujić sp. nov. (male holotype), wing. Scale bars 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/840468/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Figs 28–29</figureCitation>
). Predominantly black; tergite 1 dorsally with short and laterally with long yellowish pile; tergites 2–4 with short adpressed yellowish pile; tergite 2 slightly narrower than tergite 1 medially and nearly as long as tergite 3; anterolateral portions and posterior margin of tergite 2 yellow; posterior fifth of tergite 3 yellow; posterior fourth of tergite 4 yellow; tergite 3 with a small pair of faint greyish crescent pollinose fasciae (visible in dorsal view); tergite 4 with a pair of arched greyish pollinose fasciae; posterior margin of sternites 1–3 yellow; hypopygium black. 
<emphasis id="DBF27D5EFFC1FFD1FF15F8CFFEDC7133" bold="true" box="[229,336,1820,1845]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Genitalia</emphasis>
. Dorsal lobe of surstylus (lateral view) nearly 2.7 times longer than wide and with a distinct median U-shaped bend on inner side (dorsal view); cercus semirectangular (lateral view) and distinctly broadened medially (dorsal view) (
